08/07/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- More than half of the Serb homes damaged or destroyed in the mid-March riots have been repaired, according to Bexhet Brajsori, president of the commission responsible for the project. 
Speaking on Wednesday (7 July), he said that 263 homes have been fully repaired, while another 205 are under construction, as are schools damaged in the interethnic violence. 
He also called on the Serbian community to help the process, which he said is going according to schedule. 
(B92, KosovaLive - 07/07/04)
